summary: I... genuinely can not decide whether Detective Pikachu looks fun and just the way I imagined real-life Pokémon to look, ooor if...
body:
I… genuinely can not decide whether Detective Pikachu looks fun and just the way I imagined real-life Pokémon to look, ooor if it’s a horrible abomination that should not exist. Literally, I can not pick between the two extremes, but I’m very sure that… there is no in-between in this case…

But I’m fairly certain it’ll live on Ryan Reynolds’ performance, sooo that’s probably one to be watch in English and not in the dub…

summary: I guess were at a point in movie history where Hollywood has TRULY ran out of ideas and ANY movie can get made.  Disney remaking...
body:
I guess were at a point in movie history where Hollywood has TRULY ran out of ideas and ANY movie can get made. 

Disney remaking every one of there animated movies? Yes.

A live action Pokemon movie with Ryan Reynolds voicing Pikachu? Sure. 

A female Ghostbusters remake? Yeah.

A live action Monster Hunter Movie directed by Paul W.S Anderson? Why not?

All the kind of things people were parodying in Tropic Thunder and as April Fools jokes. 

Sooner or later this could happen.

summary: Say what you want, but the trailer delivered everything in my strong opinion. I know the CGI will not be everyone’s cup of tea,...
body: Say what you want, but the trailer delivered everything in my strong opinion. I know the CGI will not be everyone’s cup of tea, but let’s be real, if Pokemon existed in this world, they’d look like the one’s in the trailer. It had everything: humor, action, Psyduck being Psyduck, cinematography, Justice Smith nailing it as the lead, and super adorable Pikachu voiced by the great Ryan Reynolds!
